26/12/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Friday (24 December) that his country faces a "long path" to joining the EU.
However, he voiced confidence that Turkey has the necessary maturity and determination to complete the accession process successfully.
Speaking on national television, Erdogan said the European Council decision to start talks with Ankara was an important turning point, but warned that the negotiations might last longer than expected.
He pledged the government's commitment to implementing reforms.
(Anadolu Agency, AFP, Reuters - 24/12/04)
